<Page xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      Title="The Stylus-Mode Menu">
    <FlowDocumentReader ViewingMode="Scroll">
        <FlowDocument>
            <Paragraph TextAlignment="Center" FontSize="16pt">
                The Stylus-Mode Menu 
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Stylus-Mode</Bold> menu lets you control the 
                functionality of the stylus or the mouse.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Ink</Bold> option is the default. The stylus
                (or mouse with left button pressed) draws ink on the pad.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Erase by Point</Bold> option turns the stylus
                or mouse into an eraser. Erasing only affects parts of
                a stroke and effectively divides strokes into multiple 
                pieces.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Erase by Stroke</Bold> option lets you erase 
                entire strokes by touching the stylus or mouse pointer 
                to the stroke.
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                The <Bold>Select</Bold> mode lets you select strokes.
                The stylus or mouse draws a lasso that you can draw
                around one or more strokes. After the strokes are 
                selected, you can move or resize the selection box, 
                or use the
                <Hyperlink NavigateUri="EditMenu.xaml">
                    Edit menu
                </Hyperlink>
                to copy the strokes to the clipboard, delete the 
                strokes, or reformat them.
            </Paragraph>
        </FlowDocument>
    </FlowDocumentReader>
</Page>
